
[1]apple

   AP'PLE, n.

   1. The fruit of the apple tree, [pyrus malus,] from which cider is
   made.

   2. The apple of the eye is the pupil.

   Apple of love, or love apple, the tomato, or lycopersicum, a species of
   Solanum. The stalk is herbaceous, with oval, pinnated leaves, and small
   yellow flowers. The berry is smooth, soft, of a yellow or reddish
   color, of the size of a plum. It is used in soups and broths.

                     AP'PLE, v.t. To form like an apple.
